text: The only food court in this region in walking distance. Lots of choices available. M1 signal is very poor inside.

Love the "salad" fruit abalone yusheng, something out of the traditional type. Highly recommended

The pork is too tough.
The prawn paste chicken is not bad.
The fish is not fresh.
Tofu is not bad.
Fried rice is good.

Overall, food us not oily, have wok qi.
Definitely, will try again.

Very nice place. Specially " Om Shanthi Indian Food " . Very cheap and Best. I can guarantee for their idly is no -1 in Singapore . Mutton briyani really good.  If you want to eat south Indian good quality  home food better go to Om Shanthi....
Unique location of food court with dense crowd. Food is getting better with certain new outlets yet to take over.
Tze char stall price not expensive but quite nice, opens till any 7+pm.. has chicken rice, Indian food n western food at night.. busy lunch time , has a new Malay food stall now..
